                                                                                                                                                                       Mankad falters   in final
    New Delhi: Harsh Mankad and partner Scott Oudsema ended runners-up in the ATP Challenger event at Louisiana in the United States after falling to the top-seed American pair of Bobby Reynolds and Rajeev Ram.
    The Indo-American pair put up a gritty fight but lost 3-6, 7-6(8-6), 3-10 in the summit clash of the $50,000 event to the local favourites. Mankad and Oudsema earned 45 rankings points each.
    Ferrero best
    Casablanca: Juan Carlos Ferrero of Spain beat fifth-seed Florent Serra of France 6-4, 7-5 Sunday to win his first title since 2003 at the Grand Prix Hassan II.
    Ferrero won for the first time since the Madrid Masters in October 2003. That year, Ferrero won his only Grand Slam title at the French Open and lost in the US Open final to Andy Roddick.
    Jankovic wins
    Marbella: Serbian second seed Jelena Jankovic beat Spain rsquo;s Carla Suarez 6-3, 3-6, 6-3 in the final of the first edition of the $500,000 WTA Andalucia Tennis Experience clay court here on Sunday.
    Shuttlers shine
    New Delhi: Indian junior shuttlers dazzled at the Mauritius Open Invitation badminton tournament, winning all categories except the women rsquo;s doubles. Hirak Jyoti Neog and Gauri Ghate won the men rsquo;s singles and women rsquo;s singles titles respectively. The men rsquo;s doubles title was won by Hirak Jyoti and Akshit Mahajan, while Akshit and Vaishali won the mixed doubles crown.
    China on top
    Seoul: Chinese shuttlers clinched three titles at the Asia Badminton Championships in South Korea Sunday. The men rsquo;s and women rsquo;s singles finals were both all-China affairs. China secured their third title of the tournament in the women rsquo;s doubles category.
